Cloneable, GeodeticObject, NamedObject
public class ProjectionSchema
extends BaseNamedGeodeticObject

implements a projection schema containing a exemplar/template object, PE equivalent projection name, and an array of parameter schemas. A projection schema contains information on what parameters are expected within the a given projection. The following is a part of the ProjectionSchema table from the GeodeticDatabase:

  • [$Projection Schemas$, ProjectionSchema]
  • //NAME, DESCRIPTION, LONG DESCRIPTION, Java Class Name, PE Engine Name, PROJECTION INSTANTIATION VALUES
  • TM, "Transverse Mercator", "", "Transverse_Mercator", TransverseMercator, AUNIT, LUNIT, CM, LAT0, CMSF, FE, FN
  • LAMBERT2, "Lambert (2 Parallels)", "Lambert Conformal Conic (2 Parallels)", "Lambert_Conformal_Conic", LambertTwoParallels, AUNIT, LUNIT, CM, LATN, LATS, LAT0, FE, FN
  • LAMBERT1, "Lambert (1 Parallel w/Standard Parallel)", "Lambert Conformal Conic (w/Standard Parallel)", "", LambertStandardParallel, AUNIT, LUNIT, CM, STANLAT, SF, LAT0, FE, FN
  • LAMBERT11, "Lambert (1 Parallel)", "Lambert Conformal Conic (1 Parallel)", "", LambertOneParallel, AUNIT, LUNIT, CM, LAT0, SF, FE, FN
  • POLYCONIC, "Polyconic", "", "Polyconic", Polyconic, AUNIT, LUNIT, CM, LAT0, FE, FN
  • IMWPOLYCONIC, "IMW Polyconic", "", "", IMWPolyconic, AUNIT, LUNIT, CM, LATS, LATN, LON-TS, FE, FN
  • BEHRMAN, "Behrmann", "", "Behrman", Behrman, AUNIT, LUNIT, CM, FE, FN
  • BONNE, "Bonne", "", "Bonne", Bonne, AUNIT, LUNIT, CM, STANLAT, FE, FN
  • CASSINI1, "Cassini I", "", "Cassini", Cassini1, AUNIT, LUNIT, CM, CSF, LAT0, FE, FN
  • CASSINI2, "Cassini II", "", "", Cassini2, AUNIT, LUNIT, CM, LAT-TS, FE, FN
